<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-453-116  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 453 116.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Personal Computing  August 1989 v13 n8 p179(2).andM;ne</JOURNAL><TITLE>See you in court. (intellectual property lawsuits and computercrime) (View From the Valley) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Reed, Sandra R.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Intellectual-property issues are causing anxiety in the computerindustry as patenting and copyrighting of software becomeprevalent.andP;  Software developers must apply for patents as theywork and face unknowingly violating others' pending patentsbecause patent applications are confidential.andP;  Analysts say that apatent, granted in the spring of 1989 to Quarterdeck Systems forits Desqview windowing software, could cause a major shakeup inthe software industry if the company enforces it aggressively.andO;Quarterdeck is considering asking for royalties from competingproducts, such as Microsoft Windows and IBM's PresentationManager.andP;  Other companies are fighting over the microcode thatcontrols processors, disk drive architecture, and other issues.andO;Computer crime and South African trade are also briefly discussed.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer industryIntellectual PropertyCopyrightPatentSoftware PublishersComputer Crime.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>